2
00:00:54,670 --> 00:00:57,970
You said you weren't nervous at all but you were trembling.

3
00:00:57,970 --> 00:01:00,780
I didn't tremble at all.

4
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:04,200
Then why are you sitting here alone?

5
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:06,930
You're completed your first performance well.

6
00:01:06,930 --> 00:01:10,150
Shouldn't you be really happy?

7
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:17,640
What are you thinking about?

8
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:23,370
About this and that.

9
00:01:23,370 --> 00:01:26,430
I had some thoughts about when I was little.

10
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:35,530
Okay, I knew this would happen, so I prepared a present.

11
00:01:35,530 --> 00:01:37,470
A present?

12
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:40,750
Tada!  Bang, bang, bang bang!

13
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,460
You did well!

14
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:43,960
What app is that?

15
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:51,860
We can't stand on the same stage, but I can still congratulate you, like this.

16
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:54,620
♫ my heart trembles so much ♫

17
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:58,830
♫ my heart beats so much ♫

18
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:01,790
It was such a wonderful performance.

19
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:07,550
I was so envious, I could cry.

20
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:12,010
♫ on that happy day ♫

21
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:14,230
You were the coolest in the world.

22
00:02:14,230 --> 00:02:17,760
♫ to be loving you ♫

23
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:22,550
♫ I gonna love with you ♫

24
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,020
Good job.

25
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:33,920
You all worked hard today.

26
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:40,010
You did so well.  How did you do so well?

27
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:42,480
You were good today.  There might be some articles posted about you.

28
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,750
Thank you.  You worked hard.

29
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:50,580
The person that you said you liked before was...

30
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,510
I wanted to play also, like this.

31
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:54,400
You should do it.  You should.

32
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,460
You should do it.  You'll do it soon.

33
00:02:57,460 --> 00:03:00,950
You did so well.  You were remarkable.

34
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:10,410
You all did so well today.

35
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:13,420
The audience response is good, and the reporters' response is good as well.

36
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:15,240
You know that there is an after-party, right?

37
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,620
You can all head over there.

38
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:21,010
Good job.  Good job.

39
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:23,280
- Good job.
- Thank you.

40
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:25,890
- Good job.
- Good job.

41
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:34,780
Really.  They always have to make it obvious.

42
00:03:36,410 --> 00:03:40,550
Yi Yeong, where is Conductor Nam?

43
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,540
I'll go to the waiting room right now.

44
00:04:34,050 --> 00:04:36,160
Why are these flowers here?

45
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:40,590
Where did he go?

46
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,580
Conductor!

47
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:51,870
Conductor!

48
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:55,550
Conductor?

49
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:04,370
- What are you doing here?  Are you alright?
- Yes.

50
00:05:06,810 --> 00:05:09,560
Where you conducting the whole time in this condition?

51
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,110
What about Ms. Bok Bun?

52
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:15,550
In the President's room.

53
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:18,120
I should call an ambulance.

54
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:25,340
I don't need an ambulance, but get Manager Yun without letting anyone else know.

55
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,210
And I have a favor to ask.

56
00:05:28,210 --> 00:05:31,620
Make some excuse and take Bok Bun home, please.

57
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:36,110
Don't worry about that.  I'll get the Manager.

58
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,090
What about the Conductor?

59
00:05:43,090 --> 00:05:45,990
He's inside.  His condition is very bad.

60
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:48,340
Please stay with him until the Manager comes.

61
00:05:48,340 --> 00:05:50,670
I'll be in touch with you soon.

62
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:13,190
How do you feel?

63
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:16,430
What do you mean?

64
00:06:16,430 --> 00:06:19,690
The feeling of finishing your first performance well.

65
00:06:19,690 --> 00:06:21,790
How about you, Conductor?

66
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:26,240
Me?  I feel like a child again.

67
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:29,740
It makes me think about the first time I stood on stage holding a conductor's baton.

68
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:33,500
Why did you meet Yun Yeong Gil right before the performance?

69
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:36,270
Who is Yun Yeong Gil?  I don't know that person.

70
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,000
- Why did you meet someone you don't know?
- I didn't meet him.

71
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,190
You met him.  I saw it.

72
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,630
Can you prove it?

73
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:49,030
Why didn't you take a picture instead of spying on me?

74
00:06:49,030 --> 00:06:51,800
In the future, please do that.

75
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,410
Oh my goodness, look at the sweat!

76
00:07:01,410 --> 00:07:04,100
If you're sick, you should say so.  What the heck!

77
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,790
I will take him.

78
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:07,370
No, it's alright.  This is my job.

79
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:10,150
Go get Assistant Yang.

80
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:14,610
Yun, go quickly to the after-party.

81
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:26,910
If she finds out I just arrived, Mom will kill me.

82
00:07:28,010 --> 00:07:30,540
It looks like you practiced a lot.

83
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:36,770
From what I heard when it was over, the response was good.

84
00:07:36,770 --> 00:07:39,010
I heard a lot of praise for you.

85
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:40,970
The CEO left first.

86
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:47,510
He didn't say anything, but seeing you on stage, I think he felt emotional.

87
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:50,070
I felt the same, to be honest.

88
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:54,100
I thought about how happy Ian would have been if he were here.

89
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:57,200
You should stop there.  I have to go.

90
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,530
I'm leaving.

91
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,410
You worked hard.

92
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:19,930
Choi Gi Sang!

93
00:08:19,930 --> 00:08:22,040
Oh, Doctor!

94
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,130
You do know Jang Yun.

95
00:08:24,130 --> 00:08:28,670
You denied that you knew him.  How do you know each other?

96
00:08:28,670 --> 00:08:30,650
The thing is...

97
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,280
We're fr-friends.

98
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:37,810
Friends?  Why did you appear in front of me?

99
00:08:37,810 --> 00:08:41,090
- Did you appear on purpose?
- Yes.

100
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:46,190
- Coming to the blind date and coming to the hospital as a patient, all of it?
- Yes.

101
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:49,510
Why did you appear?  What were you trying to find out?

102
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:52,440
Did Jang Yun tell you to do it?

103
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:56,360
That's not it.  I did it of my own accord.

104
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,200
Why?  What was your purpose?

105
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:01,460
It's a bit difficult to tell you.

106
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:03,900
You're laughing?  Is it funny?

107
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:07,000
Why would you do something that puts you in a difficult situation?  You're not going to say?

108
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,370
I didn't mean to laugh.  I feel so sorry.

109
00:09:10,370 --> 00:09:11,710
Sorry?

110
00:09:11,710 --> 00:09:16,140
Sorry?  Don't you know you're guilty of  conspiring to deceive people and  to spy?

111
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:19,700
I didn't do anything illegal.

112
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:22,810
Listen carefully.  I won't say it again.

113
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:26,720
If you mess with my family, I will go crazy.

114
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,670
Leave Yi Yeong alone.

115
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:34,740
That's already out of my hands, so I can't do anything about it.

116
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,630
I'm sorry.

117
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,670
This is assault.

118
00:09:41,670 --> 00:09:44,810
Then report me.  Do it quickly, please do it!

119
00:09:44,810 --> 00:09:48,010
Don't appear in front of me.

120
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:52,640
If you appear again, I'll kill you.  This is a threat.

121
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,510
Yes.

122
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:57,290
You evil bastard.

123
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:10,630
- Now!
- Cheers!

124
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:12,080
Our performance today was daebak.

125
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,610
We really were the best.

126
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:18,160
- Were there any mistakes in our section?
- No way.

127
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:23,980
Today, before we started Scheherazade,  didn't you feel overwhelmed?

128
00:10:23,980 --> 00:10:27,090
The conductor looked very nervous.

129
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:31,400
I've never seen him that way before. His eyes were pitch black.

130
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:35,010
I thought he wouldn't be able to lift his baton. I felt practically hopeless.

131
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:36,160
I know, right?

132
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:39,990
But it was good. Maybe he had a catharsis?

133
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:42,000
I felt like something was pouring out of him, shall I say?

134
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,760
- Yes.
- Right.

135
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:49,130
- Yun, I loved your playing today.
- Me too!

136
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,550
Yes, it was great.

137
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:51,590
Thank you.

138
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:56,880
The reporters asked me about you.  You're not a major performer yet, so they were very surprisred.

139
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:59,400
Everyone saw the glow on Manager Yun's face?

140
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,350
We saw it.

141
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:03,350
But isn't Yi Yeong coming?

142
00:11:03,350 --> 00:11:04,600
Why?

143
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,710
Right, did Yi Yeong say she's coming?

144
00:11:06,710 --> 00:11:10,690
She's taking Conductor's grandmother home, so she will be a little late.

145
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:15,810
Shall we have a toast?

146
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:16,780
- Yes.
- Yes.

147
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:19,190
To Sinyeong Philharmonic!

148
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:21,790
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

149
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:32,190
A taxi would take me right to the door. As if I wouldn't be able to find your home!

150
00:11:32,190 --> 00:11:36,110
You didn't have to do this.

151
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:41,100
I should bring you home, of course. You're not familiar with the neighborhood.

152
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:49,100
- Feeling a bit sad, huh?
- About what?

153
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:53,740
About Conductor. You didn't have a chance to see him at all after the concert.

154
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:57,460
That boy, I don't have to see him, I'm fine.

155
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:02,400
But still... today is such a special day.

156
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:07,600
Try living as long as me. See if any days are really all that special.

157
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:13,310
You can go now. Isn't today the day for you young people to be drinking?

158
00:12:14,710 --> 00:12:16,710
I'm tired.

159
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:32,200
Mr. Tone-Deaf: Where are you? There's something I want to tell you.

160
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:38,600
Hurry and go already. You're bothering me. Go.

161
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:42,100
Go already. You're bothering me.

162
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,460
Go. Shoo.

163
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:49,000
- I will come back.
- Sure. Go.

164
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:11,340
You surprised me.

165
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:13,160
Did you sleep?

166
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,180
Yes, just dozing off, while waiting.

167
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:20,530
What about the gathering with the others?

168
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:22,730
I left for a bit. It's nearby, do you want to go?

169
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:27,690
Of course, the after-party is the "flower" of the performance.

170
00:13:27,690 --> 00:13:29,820
Let's not go.

171
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:33,810
What will we do instead?

172
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:35,740
We'll figure something out.

173
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,900
- One, two...
- One, two ...

174
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,400
Up.

175
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,790
But why did we come here?

176
00:13:55,790 --> 00:14:00,450
Just wanted to come to the stage with you.

177
00:14:02,890 --> 00:14:06,380
Someday we will stand on the same stage, right?

178
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:20,260
Maybe after being reborn a million times, if we meet again?

179
00:14:22,330 --> 00:14:25,070
Think positively.

180
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:34,600
What was it that you wanted to tell me today?

181
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,710
Huh?

182
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:40,350
That's what you texted me earlier today.

183
00:14:44,330 --> 00:14:49,730
I feel like I've made you suffer too much, Yi Yeong.

184
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,800
All of a sudden?

185
00:14:54,330 --> 00:15:00,960
I suspected you endlessly, hated you, and accused you.

186
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:03,200
I did that.

187
00:15:05,310 --> 00:15:08,520
But you couldn't help it, based on the situation.

188
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:13,080
"I shouldn't ever have appeared in front of Yi Yeong."

189
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,430
I have regrets like that.

190
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:20,780
I keep wondering if there was some better way.

191
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:25,790
If that was case, we may have never met,

192
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:27,570
perhaps?

193
00:15:29,420 --> 00:15:33,880
But I'm happy to have met you. I guess you don't feel the same, Yun?

194
00:15:38,060 --> 00:15:40,790
When did you meet Yun Yeong Gil?

195
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:45,750
That man?

196
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:48,360
That man spoke to me.

197
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:54,610
You aren't the person who killed Ian.

198
00:15:55,460 --> 00:15:59,000
He didn't die because you stabbed him.

199
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,920
Someone else killed him.

200
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:10,970
So now you can discard the guilt over killing Ian.

201
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,370
You can throw it all away.

202
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:17,390
Your heart should be a peace.

203
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:20,080
Yes.

204
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:26,800
- Ummm ....Yun.
- Huh?

205
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,130
It's nothing.

206
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:11,000
♫ Because your calm eyes are deeper than a lake ♫

207
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:17,610
♫ If  something sad is said, you are swayed like a wave ♫

208
00:17:17,610 --> 00:17:22,740
Do you have a ballpoint pen distributed as a gift by the Sinyeong College of Music?

209
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:26,750
♫ ... like walking through a green forest ♫

210
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:32,460
♫ I can never get tired ♫

211
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:39,700
♫ I love the moment and lI'll live looking forward to eternity ♫

212
00:17:40,990 --> 00:17:43,010
Have a good performance.

213
00:17:43,010 --> 00:17:46,540
It's alright if you make a mistake, so don't be nervous.

214
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:50,230
I'm not even the main player, so I just have to do what I always did.

215
00:17:50,230 --> 00:17:54,800
It's the same as being the main character. When you play the first encore ...

216
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:58,470
♫  Please let me hear your song.  ♫

217
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:03,330
Tada!  Bang bang bang bang!  You did well!
♫ So that I can love you more. I want to treasure it  ♫

218
00:18:03,330 --> 00:18:05,500
♫  alone for a long time ♫

219
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:09,230
♫ Before this feeling wanes ♫

220
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:15,410
♫ Please take my hand so that I won't get weary ♫

221
00:18:15,410 --> 00:18:18,350
♫ You take me all. ♫

222
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:37,320
♫ You take me all ♫

223
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:43,330
Yun Yeong Gil Repayment

224
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:20,960
Grandmother, when did you finish cooking?

225
00:19:21,980 --> 00:19:26,270
When, this thing!  You were fast asleep.

226
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:28,810
It's gotten cold.

227
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:32,410
The refrigerator was empty.  What did you put in to boil?

228
00:19:32,410 --> 00:19:37,220
I put an egg and some drief up onion and boiled them.

229
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:43,550
I should have brought the side dishes to your house and not Ju Wan's.

230
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:47,110
He's not going to eat them anyway.

231
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:48,790
Wash your face.  Wash up and come to eat.

232
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:50,890
Yes.

233
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:56,430
Go-fer.

234
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:07,320
Were you crying in the early morning?

235
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,390
Huh?

236
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:14,900
I thought it was you but I guess it was a cat crying.

237
00:20:20,070 --> 00:20:23,020
No, Grandmother.

238
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:28,500
Today at around 4 a.m, the body of a man in his forties was found in the building of the Sinyeong Philharmonic Orchestra.

239
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:30,760
- Sinyeong Philharmonic?
- The police are investigating.

240
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:35,200
According to the Gyeonggiseobu Station, the victim is Mr. Yun, 45 years old, unemployed.

241
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,300
While the police are placing priority on missing persons,

242
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:40,840
What happened?

243
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:44,630
an autopsy has been requested of the National Forensic Service to accurately determine the cause of death.

244
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:47,210
What's the matter?

245
00:20:50,170 --> 00:20:52,900
Are you alright?

246
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:56,020
Just a moment.

247
00:21:03,610 --> 00:21:07,600
`The body of a man in his 40s was found in the Sinyoung Philharmonic Orchestra building.

248
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:21,210
What's the matter?

249
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:25,400
I think he is dead.  In our orchestra's building.

250
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,030
It was just on the news.

251
00:21:28,030 --> 00:21:31,480
It's because of me. I think he died because of me.

252
00:21:32,820 --> 00:21:35,380
Come in. Come.

253
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:42,010
Take a seat.

254
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:47,020
What do you mean by saying you think he died because of you?

255
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:53,300
- I lied to you.
- Are you saying you lied?

256
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:58,440
Actually, I did meet him again. Not at the flower shop.  And then ...

257
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:02,500
Then, again, why?  Why did you meet him?

258
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:08,520
The object he was searching for ... I knew what it was.

259
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,360
He told me.

260
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:14,080
When I ran into him in front of the flower shop, I asked him what it was.

261
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:19,250
Did he just tell you what it was?

262
00:22:20,770 --> 00:22:22,900
He told me.

263
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:27,260
He asked me to find it and take it to him.

264
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:31,310
If I did that, he would tell me who was in the warehouse that day.

265
00:22:31,310 --> 00:22:33,680
And so?

266
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,380
It  was ...

267
00:22:37,530 --> 00:22:40,540
I found it and gave it to him.

268
00:22:40,540 --> 00:22:42,260
What was it?

269
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:46,620
A ballpoing pen made as a gift by the Sinyeong Music College.

270
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:57,930
That day you came and asked to look at Ian's belongings,

271
00:22:57,930 --> 00:23:01,760
you found and snuck it away without saying anything?

272
00:23:02,530 --> 00:23:04,370
I'm sorry.

273
00:23:06,490 --> 00:23:08,920
So, did you really give it to him?

274
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:12,490
I did.

275
00:23:12,490 --> 00:23:14,870
Did he tell you who was in the warehousse that day?

276
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:20,100
No.  He said he changed his mind. He thought he could get more money by not telling me.

277
00:23:20,150 --> 00:23:22,840
Of course, he wouldn't just tell you.

278
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:28,490
Just what were you thinking? You should have told me first.

279
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:31,800
It's because I wanted to know who was in the warehouse.

280
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:35,060
He might have been Ian's murderer.

281
00:23:35,060 --> 00:23:39,270
If you really wanted to know the culprit,  you should have looked for yourself at the object he was looking for.

282
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:42,750
That's the way to have found out.  Do you agree?

283
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,360
How could you give it to him?

284
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,350
I'm sorry.

285
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:56,980
For now, go home.

286
00:23:56,980 --> 00:24:01,520
Don't say anything and go to work as usual.  Alright?

287
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:02,840
Yes.

288
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:05,750
Go now.  Get up.

289
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:11,690
Next news.   It turns out that  Mr. Yun , whose body was found at the Sinyeong Philharmonic Orchestra building,

290
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:16,800
was the driver of the car  which killed pianist Kim Ian in a hit-and-run accident one year ago.

291
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:20,300
Although the police have not discovered a connection between the two cases,

292
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:24,700
it's known that the scope of the investigation has been expanded from a simple fall  to murder.

293
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:30,270
I am sorry but the incident here has nothing to do with the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

294
00:24:30,270 --> 00:24:33,010
It really doesn't.

295
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:34,620
Yes?

296
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:40,700
Today's incident is a simple falling  accident which has nothing to do with the Sihyeong Philharmonic. I'm sorry.

297
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:45,540
Yes.  There really is no connection.

298
00:24:51,650 --> 00:24:53,610
Did you see it?

299
00:24:55,300 --> 00:25:00,400
Yu Da:  The detectives are in the security office.  They are getting all the cameta footage!

300
00:25:05,890 --> 00:25:07,950
What is this?

301
00:25:13,860 --> 00:25:17,360
The body of a man in his 40's was found at the Sinyeong Philharmonic Orchestra building.

302
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:26,390
Manager, this has nothing to do with our orchestra, does it?

303
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:29,770
If it's Kim Ian, he is someone who collaborated with the Asia Philharmonic last year.

304
00:25:29,770 --> 00:25:35,140
He was killed in a hit-and-run accident.  Aren't  they saying  the hir-and-run driver died here?

305
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:41,100
Today's rehearsal is cancelled. The accident at the building is a simple accident.

306
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:45,800
It has no connection to the Sinyeong Philharmonic so everyone, don't get agitated.

307
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:50,400
I beg you to please not spread what happened outside of here as much as possible.

308
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:03,500
Conductor?

309
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:08,100
What's the matter with your face?  Can I come in?

310
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:10,410
Yes.

311
00:26:12,890 --> 00:26:16,120
Goddess, I'm here.

312
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:19,250
Our Bok Bun.  I was dying to see you.

313
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:23,200
Child, you're such a smooth talker.

314
00:26:24,910 --> 00:26:26,860
Did you see the news?

315
00:26:26,860 --> 00:26:32,310
I heard a man was found dead in your orchestra building.

316
00:26:34,190 --> 00:26:36,860
Yes.  I saw it.

317
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:41,900
Whoever it might be, it's caused a lot of noise today.  We don't have a rehearsal today.

318
00:26:44,570 --> 00:26:46,910
This is delicious. Give me some rice.

319
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:49,400
Yes.

320
00:26:57,850 --> 00:27:00,390
Why don't you stay and sleep over for another day?

321
00:27:00,390 --> 00:27:03,540
How could I keep my restaurant closed for another day?

322
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:07,810
We should have dinner there.  There are people waiting.

323
00:27:11,290 --> 00:27:14,550
Shall I follow you and live there?

324
00:27:16,150 --> 00:27:18,320
I'll help you with the restaurant and teach kids.

325
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:21,750
The sound of an out-of-work crazy man.

326
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:24,080
You can't  make a living there.

327
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:27,160
Rest your bones in Seoul.

328
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:40,190
Are you going to work?

329
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:43,320
Yes.

330
00:27:47,830 --> 00:27:50,580
You go to work together with him, too.

331
00:27:50,580 --> 00:27:53,760
Because of the news, the orchestra is going to be a mess.

332
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:57,910
So the conductor should hurry over and protect his position.

333
00:27:57,910 --> 00:27:59,170
Go. Give me that.

334
00:27:59,170 --> 00:28:01,620
Go-fer, follow me.

335
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:03,820
I need you to walk with me.  Quickly leave.

336
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:04,970
Leave.  Let's leave.

337
00:28:04,970 --> 00:28:07,020
I'm leaving.

338
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:18,810
Do you want a ride to work?

339
00:28:18,810 --> 00:28:20,940
How did you kill him?

340
00:28:22,890 --> 00:28:25,560
Did you just push him off the building?

341
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,670
Who killed whom?

342
00:28:26,670 --> 00:28:31,580
I'm sure you know where there are no cameras in the building because you know the building. I also know.

343
00:28:32,730 --> 00:28:34,460
Don't laugh.

344
00:28:34,460 --> 00:28:38,180
I saw you meeting Yun Yeong Gil.  You met just before the concert.

345
00:28:38,180 --> 00:28:40,250
Was it because of what he had?

346
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:42,890
Did you take it?

347
00:28:42,890 --> 00:28:45,190
What is it that I took?

348
00:28:45,190 --> 00:28:50,590
What's this about my killing someone I don't even know?

349
00:28:50,590 --> 00:28:53,690
Just tell me. The truth will become known anyway.

350
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:55,790
What are you holding?

351
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:59,090
What the hell did you do that you killed two people?

352
00:28:59,090 --> 00:29:02,380
I have no idea what the hell you are talking about.

353
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:07,470
Two people are dead.  How can you act as though nothing happened?

354
00:29:07,470 --> 00:29:10,200
You were the person in the warehouse that day, weren't you?

355
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:14,280
You were afraid he would tell Hong Yi Yeong your name, so   you killed him?

356
00:29:16,670 --> 00:29:19,610
Behave in  moderation.  It's not just once or twice.

357
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:23,730
If you're going to say something in front of me, next time, bring the evidence.

358
00:29:25,710 --> 00:29:32,730
How can you remain cool in front of Hong Yi Yeong after killing Ian?

359
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:35,490
You give me the creeps.

360
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:51,570
Jang Yun.  Don't talk nonsense when you don't know anything.

361
00:29:51,570 --> 00:29:54,950
Kim Ian was precious to me too.

362
00:29:54,950 --> 00:30:00,050
I first met him in England and I knew him for ten years.

363
00:30:00,050 --> 00:30:03,070
He was my only friend.

364
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:08,170
How could I have killed him?

365
00:30:09,590 --> 00:30:11,330
If you didn't kill him, who did?

366
00:30:11,330 --> 00:30:16,170
How many times are you going to say that? How do I know?
